WEBVTT

00:02.830 --> 00:04.250
Tragic news out of Washington
this morning --

00:04.250 --> 00:05.540
Vice President Luna Vargas
has died

00:05.540 --> 00:06.620
of an apparent heart attack.

00:06.620 --> 00:07.750
The question now is
who will become

00:07.750 --> 00:09.790
this country's next
Vice President.

00:09.790 --> 00:11.960
After a speedy confirmation,
it's official --

00:11.960 --> 00:13.670
Cyrus Rutherford Beene
has been sworn in

00:13.670 --> 00:15.750
as the country's next
Vice President.

00:15.750 --> 00:17.120
Well, folks,
President Mellie Grant

00:17.120 --> 00:19.120
certainly came out swinging
last night

00:19.120 --> 00:22.040
with her very first address
to a joint session of Congress.

00:22.040 --> 00:23.750
Grant's remarks on everything
from healthcare

00:23.750 --> 00:25.920
to foreign policy
to uniting the country

00:25.920 --> 00:28.460
left many wondering how,
exactly,

00:28.460 --> 00:30.040
she's gonna get it all done.

00:30.040 --> 00:32.790
[ Tone-Loc's "Funky Cold Medina"
plays ]

00:32.790 --> 00:39.880
♪♪

00:39.880 --> 00:41.750
The aim of
President Grant's

00:41.750 --> 00:43.330
very first
legislative initiative

00:43.330 --> 00:45.250
is to give free education
to every American --

00:45.250 --> 00:46.960
And by "free,"
you mean "worse," right?

00:46.960 --> 00:48.670
If President Grant
and Olivia Pope

00:48.670 --> 00:51.120
are somehow able to
pull off the impossible

00:51.120 --> 00:53.620
and, God forbid,
get this bill passed,

00:53.620 --> 00:55.000
then the state of education,

00:55.000 --> 00:57.460
like everything else that's been
made free and undervalued,

00:57.460 --> 00:58.830
will start to decline.

00:58.830 --> 01:00.620
I, for one,
will not stand of it.

01:00.620 --> 01:02.710
♪ Havin' drinks with
some no-name chump ♪

01:02.710 --> 01:04.710
♪ When they know that
I'm the star ♪

01:04.710 --> 01:06.420
♪ So I got up
and strolled over ♪

01:06.420 --> 01:09.040
♪ To the other side
of the cantina ♪

01:09.040 --> 01:10.750
♪ I asked the guy,
"Why you so fly?" ♪

01:10.750 --> 01:13.330
♪ He said, "Funky Cold Medina" ♪

01:13.330 --> 01:17.080
Senator Michaels,
thank you for being punctual.

01:17.080 --> 01:19.670
Summoning me
to the principal's office

01:19.670 --> 01:21.540
isn't gonna get me to
change my opinion

01:21.540 --> 01:22.960
about this bill,
Ms. Pope.

01:22.960 --> 01:25.080
Oh, that's okay.
I don't care about your opinion.

01:25.080 --> 01:26.540
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
What I care about is your vote.

01:26.540 --> 01:27.960
I'm voting no.

01:27.960 --> 01:29.750
Hmm.
It's going to have to be a yes.

01:29.750 --> 01:31.710
My vote is no.
That's final.

01:31.710 --> 01:33.210
No. You need to vote yes.

01:33.210 --> 01:34.710
Now, you hold on there a minute,
missy.

01:34.710 --> 01:36.210
In what world --

01:36.210 --> 01:38.080
Before you do all of...that,

01:38.080 --> 01:40.040
you should know
that I have an envelope.

01:40.040 --> 01:41.580
See?

01:41.580 --> 01:43.580
It's packed with
a great deal of information --

01:43.580 --> 01:45.670
photos, copies of e-mails,
reports,

01:45.670 --> 01:48.750
a couple of
fascinating videos.

01:48.750 --> 01:51.710
This envelope is hot.

01:51.710 --> 01:53.290
This envelope makes careers.

01:53.290 --> 01:55.710
Not mine, because, well,
I'm already me.

01:55.710 --> 01:58.460
And it certainly won't
make yours, Senator.

01:58.460 --> 02:01.290
You know whose career
this envelope will make?

02:01.290 --> 02:04.750
Journalists --
lots of journalists.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.540
It'll also benefit
your wife.

02:06.540 --> 02:08.120
She gets the truth.

02:08.120 --> 02:09.380
How do you think
she'll react?

02:09.380 --> 02:10.880
I think she gets mad --

02:10.880 --> 02:12.290
finally lets go
of all that

02:12.290 --> 02:15.120
cleave-unto-one's-husband crap
you spout,

02:15.120 --> 02:17.500
because, let's face it --
even Jesus would tell her

02:17.500 --> 02:19.080
to leave a man who does
what's in there.

02:19.080 --> 02:23.170
Miss Pope,
ma'am, you can not --

02:23.170 --> 02:24.290
This is blackmail,
and I --

02:24.290 --> 02:25.750
Mine.

02:25.750 --> 02:26.960
What?

02:26.960 --> 02:29.790
Before you asked
"In what world" --

02:29.790 --> 02:33.170
I'm answering "Mine,"
in my world.

02:33.170 --> 02:35.210
This is my world.

02:35.210 --> 02:37.670
You're in
my envelope-filled world.

02:37.670 --> 02:39.120
♪ That's why I found
you don't play around ♪

02:39.120 --> 02:41.880
♪ With the Funky Cold Medina ♪
Mine.

02:41.880 --> 02:45.000
And in my world,

02:45.000 --> 02:47.710
which way do we vote
on free college, Senator?

02:47.710 --> 02:50.620
♪ Funky Cold Medina ♪

02:50.620 --> 02:51.620
Yes.

02:51.620 --> 02:54.290
Yes.

02:54.290 --> 02:57.670
[ Envelope rustles ]

03:03.670 --> 03:06.000
Senator Michaels is a yes
on the Vargas bill.

03:06.000 --> 03:07.920
-That's fantastic.
-Nicely done!

03:07.920 --> 03:09.620
That leaves us,
what, 12 votes shy?

03:09.620 --> 03:11.040
Is that a problem?
-No problem at all --

03:11.040 --> 03:12.920
7 of the 12 come from states
who favor this bill.

03:12.920 --> 03:14.540
It's the other five
that concern me.

03:14.540 --> 03:16.000
So, let's hit the airways,

03:16.000 --> 03:18.250
put the spotlight on
some of these hold-outs.

03:18.250 --> 03:20.420
Already on it -- I have
coms orchestrating
a social-media blitz,

03:20.420 --> 03:22.460
and a spot booked on
"Pryce of Power."

03:22.460 --> 03:24.620
Smart.
Pryce gets a lot of eyeballs.

03:24.620 --> 03:26.710
I'll be happy to get in front of
his camera.

03:26.710 --> 03:29.540
Uh -- Uh, we were thinking that
Liv could do the TV rounds,

03:29.540 --> 03:31.500
and you could whip up the votes
on the hill --

03:31.500 --> 03:32.920
work your magic,

03:32.920 --> 03:34.210
twist some arms
behind closed doors.

03:34.210 --> 03:35.500
We thought you could start
with Greenwald.

03:35.500 --> 03:37.750
-Mm.
-Did we? Well...

03:40.540 --> 03:41.880
[ Stammers ]
...w-wherever we need me.

03:45.540 --> 03:46.880
No!

03:46.880 --> 03:48.790
David, please.
We're suffering here.

03:48.790 --> 03:50.380
-You have friends.
-Who told you that?

03:50.380 --> 03:52.580
Important friends,
high-profile friends --

03:52.580 --> 03:53.880
Are you really gonna
sit there and tell us

03:53.880 --> 03:55.330
none of them have a problem
in need of fixing?

03:55.330 --> 03:57.170
-Affairs to hide?
-Dirty secrets to protect?

03:57.170 --> 03:58.210
Murders to cover up?

03:58.210 --> 03:59.830
The only problem
in need of fixing here

03:59.830 --> 04:01.830
is that you decided to change
the name of this place.

04:01.830 --> 04:03.460
It's one letter.

04:03.460 --> 04:05.540
Olivia Pope and Associates
is legend in this town.

04:05.540 --> 04:07.420
You trust OPA.

04:07.420 --> 04:09.330
Quinn Perkins and Associates --
What is that?

04:09.330 --> 04:11.460
QPA?
It's a babysitting service.

04:11.460 --> 04:12.920
Or cupcakes.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.210
It's cupcakes delivered by
babysitters.

04:14.210 --> 04:15.710
Did you just call me
a babysitter?

04:15.710 --> 04:16.960
He's a waste of time.

04:16.960 --> 04:18.330
We need to start advertising,
hit the airwaves.

04:18.330 --> 04:20.380
Been told my whole life
I've got a voice for radio.

04:20.380 --> 04:22.540
More of those or switch it up?
-Baby's maybe feeling a yogurt.

04:22.540 --> 04:26.170
David, so help me, you're not
leaving until we get a client.

04:26.170 --> 04:28.290
[ Door opens ]
-Excuse me?

04:28.290 --> 04:30.830
I-I'm looking for
Quinn Perkins and Associates?

04:30.830 --> 04:33.120
Yes. Hello!

04:33.120 --> 04:35.830
Oh, thank God.
Um, are you available?

04:35.830 --> 04:38.880
Get lost, David.

04:38.880 --> 04:40.790
My dad,
he's been overseas

04:40.790 --> 04:43.290
leading a religious studies
symposium.
Mm-hmm.

04:43.290 --> 04:45.500
He calls me every day
after his class no matter what.

04:45.500 --> 04:48.500
And then two days ago,
nothing -- no call.

04:48.500 --> 04:51.040
Well, he may have just
lost communication,

04:51.040 --> 04:52.460
a problem with his cellphone
overseas.

04:52.460 --> 04:55.540
No, this isn't
a regular overseas...

04:55.540 --> 04:57.000
My father's in Bashran.

04:57.000 --> 05:00.620
[ Sighs ]

05:00.620 --> 05:03.540
Your father's in Bashran --
like, Bashran Bashran?

05:03.540 --> 05:05.750
I-I know,
but he's a scholar.

05:05.750 --> 05:07.080
And this isn't
his first trip.

05:07.080 --> 05:09.080
He teaches there regularly.
He knows the place.

05:09.080 --> 05:10.250
He knows how to be in touch,

05:10.250 --> 05:12.080
so if he's not calling,
then something is wrong.

05:14.330 --> 05:16.620
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

05:16.620 --> 05:18.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:18.210 --> 05:19.210
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:19.210 --> 05:20.500
You're late.

05:20.500 --> 05:22.380
I'm -- I'm sorry. I...

05:22.380 --> 05:24.880
[ Chuckles ]

05:24.880 --> 05:26.380
...lost track of time.

05:26.380 --> 05:28.040
There's no need
to apologize.

05:28.040 --> 05:33.620
I just, uh...I mean,
I didn't mean to be late.

05:33.620 --> 05:37.500
"Lafeyette."
'91. Bordeaux.

05:37.500 --> 05:39.830
Yes. Lafayette '91.
Bordeaux.

05:44.580 --> 05:45.830
It's good to see you.

05:45.830 --> 05:48.500
Good to be
out of the house.

05:48.500 --> 05:49.920
You can leave the house.

05:49.920 --> 05:51.420
And go to my workplace.

05:51.420 --> 05:53.080
You can go wherever you want,
Dad.

05:53.080 --> 05:55.040
Because you have cameras on me
at all times.

05:55.040 --> 05:56.290
How many times
are we going to...

05:56.290 --> 05:57.880
[ Laughs ]

05:57.880 --> 05:59.880
I don't
have cameras on you.

05:59.880 --> 06:02.170
Olivia,
cameras are Chapter 1

06:02.170 --> 06:04.290
of the "How to
Imprison Your Dad Handbook."

06:04.290 --> 06:07.460
Cameras would mean
that I think you might run,

06:07.460 --> 06:08.960
which would be silly.

06:08.960 --> 06:11.790
Cameras would mean that
you're not heeding my advice --

06:11.790 --> 06:13.420
which would be a mistake.

06:13.420 --> 06:16.330
Cameras would mean I believe
that you don't enjoy

06:16.330 --> 06:18.040
having dinner with your daughter
every week...

06:18.040 --> 06:20.170
which would hurt.

06:24.170 --> 06:25.210
Ask me about work.

06:25.210 --> 06:26.750
How is work?

06:26.750 --> 06:28.670
Good.
I think we have a real shot

06:28.670 --> 06:31.580
at getting Vargas'
free college bill through.

06:31.580 --> 06:32.960
So you got Senator Michaels.

06:32.960 --> 06:35.080
Did he put up a fight, or did he
stand down with a whimper?

06:35.080 --> 06:37.040
I presented Senator Michaels
with the facts,

06:37.040 --> 06:38.790
and I'm thrilled that
he saw the light.

06:38.790 --> 06:40.500
The light.
[ Chuckles ]

06:40.500 --> 06:42.540
That light is something.

06:42.540 --> 06:44.580
How is the President?

06:44.580 --> 06:45.710
Mellie is good.

06:45.710 --> 06:48.960
So,
Mellie is in formation.

06:48.960 --> 06:50.830
Happy to let you
hold all the cards,

06:50.830 --> 06:53.500
wield all the power --
happy as your puppet.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.580
Mellie and I
are a team.

06:55.580 --> 06:58.080
You don't play team sports,
never have -- not well, anyway.

06:58.080 --> 07:01.170
Dad, it's my turn.

07:01.170 --> 07:02.380
I'm changing the rules.

07:02.380 --> 07:05.420
This, what I'm doing,
is better.

07:05.420 --> 07:07.170
Hmm. [ Chuckles ]

07:07.170 --> 07:10.500
You are like looking into
the window of my past.

07:10.500 --> 07:12.120
You are me.

07:12.120 --> 07:18.170
No matter how much I tried,
all I could create was me.

07:18.170 --> 07:24.040
♪♪

07:24.040 --> 07:27.420
There is a reckoning
coming for you, Olivia.

07:27.420 --> 07:28.670
You think...

07:28.670 --> 07:30.250
[ Bottle clinks ]
...you have it under control.

07:30.250 --> 07:33.330
You think you have all the power
buttoned up inside you

07:33.330 --> 07:35.830
behind your eyes,
lighting you up.

07:35.830 --> 07:37.330
But one day you'll glance
into a mirror,

07:37.330 --> 07:41.210
and you will discover that
some of that power is missing.

07:41.210 --> 07:42.920
The lights are going out.

07:42.920 --> 07:44.920
Then? You'll have some
difficult decisions to make.

07:44.920 --> 07:46.420
Do I want that power back?

07:46.420 --> 07:48.120
Who am I willing to hurt
to get it?

07:48.120 --> 07:51.380
Now I can say this
because I know --

07:51.380 --> 07:56.670
You cannot have it all,
Olivia.

07:56.670 --> 08:03.040
♪♪

08:03.040 --> 08:04.620
Watch me.

08:09.880 --> 08:11.330
-"The whole people" --
-Please don't quote me Adams.

08:11.330 --> 08:12.500
"The whole people be willing to
take upon themselves

08:12.500 --> 08:13.830
the education"...
-[ Sighs ]

08:13.830 --> 08:14.710
-..."of the whole people"...
-She's quoting Adams.

08:14.710 --> 08:15.920
..."and must be willing to bear
the expenses of it."

08:15.920 --> 08:16.920
Terrific. Bravo.
Founding fathers.

08:16.920 --> 08:19.750
I am very impressed.
My question --

08:19.750 --> 08:21.330
Yes, Curtis,
what is your question?

08:21.330 --> 08:23.080
Who pays for it?
Who gets stuck with the check?

08:23.080 --> 08:24.460
The ones
who can afford it --

08:24.460 --> 08:27.250
corporations who've gone decades
without paying taxes.

08:27.250 --> 08:29.290
"Sacrifice" wasn't always
a bad word in this country.

08:29.290 --> 08:31.460
Why is it always
Washington elites constantly

08:31.460 --> 08:33.830
lecturing regular folks on
what they should sacrifice?

08:33.830 --> 08:36.540
Was that your Mercedes I parked
next to this morning?

08:36.540 --> 08:37.830
My mom is an immigrant.

08:37.830 --> 08:39.580
My father
was a longshoreman.

08:39.580 --> 08:42.290
I was the first in my family
to go to college at 24,

08:42.290 --> 08:44.880
after I volunteered building
shelters in Central America.

08:44.880 --> 08:46.880
I could spend
the next six shows

08:46.880 --> 08:49.120
dismantling your anecdotal
systemically racist,

08:49.120 --> 08:51.750
"pull yourself up by
the boot straps" argument.

08:51.750 --> 08:54.040
But I'll keep it simple --
It doesn't fly.

08:54.040 --> 08:55.620
I wasn't ready for college
at 18.

08:55.620 --> 08:57.880
It's reasonable many Americans
don't want to foot the bill

08:57.880 --> 08:59.000
for someone's
six-year keg party.

08:59.000 --> 09:00.250
That's very narrow thinking,
Curtis.

09:00.250 --> 09:01.500
And your head is in the clouds,
Ms. Pope.

09:01.500 --> 09:02.580
Do you honestly believe
what you're saying?

09:02.580 --> 09:04.120
I don't say anything
I don't mean.

09:04.120 --> 09:07.080
That's why I'm sitting where I
am, and you're Olivia Pope.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.880
Okay, you are
supremely talented.

09:08.880 --> 09:10.920
But keeping it real?
[ Scoffs ]

09:10.920 --> 09:12.040
It ain't
one of your talents.

09:12.040 --> 09:13.920
I think you're losing
your audience,

09:13.920 --> 09:15.540
but to get back on track --

09:15.540 --> 09:18.250
college is a benefit to almost
every individual who attends.

09:18.250 --> 09:20.460
So, if we're telling it
like it is,

09:20.460 --> 09:22.540
let me run down some numbers,
real facts that will actually --

09:22.540 --> 09:24.960
Unfortunately, that's all
the time we have here today.

09:24.960 --> 09:27.330
Thank you, Ms. Pope,
for coming on to the show.

09:27.330 --> 09:28.750
We'll see you tomorrow --

09:28.750 --> 09:31.920
Same time, same Pryce,
more power.

09:31.920 --> 09:33.880
-We're clear.
-We still had 30 seconds.

09:33.880 --> 09:35.210
Oh, did we?

09:35.210 --> 09:37.040
I could've used
those 30 seconds.

09:37.040 --> 09:38.880
-I think you made your point.
-I think you made your point.

09:38.880 --> 09:39.880
I appreciate it.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.040
Your point being
that you can't stand

09:41.040 --> 09:42.710
getting schooled
on your own show.

09:42.710 --> 09:43.920
30 more seconds
would've given me

09:43.920 --> 09:45.620
30 more chances
to watch you squirm.

09:45.620 --> 09:48.120
[ Scoffs ]
[ Laughing ]

09:48.120 --> 09:49.920
You don't quit,
do you, Ms. Pope?

09:49.920 --> 09:51.420
You have no idea.

09:51.420 --> 09:55.580
♪♪

09:55.580 --> 09:57.670
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

09:57.670 --> 10:00.120
Joshua Stewart --
PhD from Princeton,

10:00.120 --> 10:02.540
professor of Comparative
Theology at Georgetown,

10:02.540 --> 10:03.790
known for doing field work

10:03.790 --> 10:05.500
in some of
the roughest places on Earth.

10:05.500 --> 10:06.790
No kidding --
Nicaragua in the '80s,

10:06.790 --> 10:08.460
Eastern Europe in the '90s,
Iraq.

10:08.460 --> 10:10.210
Not bad for an egghead.
-After his wife died,

10:10.210 --> 10:12.460
he even took little Madeline
on some of his expeditions.

10:12.460 --> 10:14.830
Aww. Daddy-daughter trips
to all the hot zones.

10:14.830 --> 10:16.210
Wait, how old do you think
our kid needs to be

10:16.210 --> 10:17.420
before we can take it
to Myanmar?

10:17.420 --> 10:19.120
2? 2 1/2?
-Stewart was last seen

10:19.120 --> 10:20.920
at the university
that hosted the symposium.

10:20.920 --> 10:22.500
Huck, can you hack into
its security system?

10:22.500 --> 10:25.420
You expect me to just break into
the government facilities

10:25.420 --> 10:27.420
of one of the most mysterious
and impenetrable

10:27.420 --> 10:29.040
nations on the planet?

10:29.040 --> 10:31.710
You guys
take me for granted.

10:31.710 --> 10:34.210
[ Keyboard clacking ]

10:34.210 --> 10:36.880
Charlie: Shy guy.

10:38.460 --> 10:39.620
Here's something.

10:39.620 --> 10:41.000
He sat on the same bench,

10:41.000 --> 10:42.670
next to the same man
two days in a row.

10:42.670 --> 10:43.580
What -- Who's his buddy?

10:43.580 --> 10:45.120
Wrong question.

10:45.120 --> 10:47.000
Right question is
"Who is on that same bench

10:47.000 --> 10:48.880
at the same time
the very next day?"

10:48.880 --> 10:50.460
The day after
Stewart disappeared?

10:50.460 --> 10:52.210
[ Keyboard clacking ]

10:52.210 --> 10:54.120
What do you see?

10:54.120 --> 10:55.460
Nothing.
I mean, there's no one.

10:55.460 --> 10:56.750
There. Stewart's pal.

10:56.750 --> 10:58.170
Well, can you get an ID
on that guy?

10:58.170 --> 10:59.670
I have enough definition
for a QR scan,

10:59.670 --> 11:01.500
but it'll come up empty.

11:01.500 --> 11:03.420
-Wait. Why?
-The secret meetings, the --

11:03.420 --> 11:05.170
the hyper-awareness of
all the surveillance cams,

11:05.170 --> 11:06.920
passport full of
gnarly stamps.

11:06.920 --> 11:08.750
Exactly.
He's a fellow traveler.

11:08.750 --> 11:10.790
Oh! No way.
That's good.

11:10.790 --> 11:13.670
Fellow traveler -- What the hell
is a fellow traveler?

11:13.670 --> 11:15.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

11:15.250 --> 11:16.460
[ Knock on door ]

11:16.460 --> 11:18.120
Quinn, it's late.

11:18.120 --> 11:19.790
Exactly, which is how you know
this is something,

11:19.790 --> 11:21.790
a something you don't want
any calls or e-mails about

11:21.790 --> 11:23.500
because...GITMO.

11:23.500 --> 11:24.790
Also, I need to pee.

11:24.790 --> 11:25.880
I was driving by.
Can I come in?

11:25.880 --> 11:27.120
What do you want, Quinn?

11:27.120 --> 11:28.920
We have a client --
missing person,

11:28.920 --> 11:30.210
but the thing is
[Inhales]

11:30.210 --> 11:31.620
we're pretty sure
he's one of yours.

11:31.620 --> 11:33.750
What do you mean
"One of mine?"

11:33.750 --> 11:35.880
He's a spy.

11:35.880 --> 11:37.120
CIA we think.

11:37.120 --> 11:38.880
We could be wrong,
but if we're not --

11:38.880 --> 11:40.120
I'll see what
I can find out.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.960
We're doing everything we can
on our end --
Quinn, I said I'm on it.

11:41.960 --> 11:43.830
Thank you.
Look, I really need to pee.

11:46.330 --> 11:47.750
Ohh.

11:47.750 --> 11:50.080
"How you doing, Quinn?
How pregnancy?"

11:50.080 --> 11:51.540
[ Sighs ]

11:51.540 --> 11:53.460
"How's my godchild doing
in there?"

11:53.460 --> 11:54.960
Rude. [ Sighs ]

11:54.960 --> 11:57.540
Jake: What's that?
Work --

11:57.540 --> 11:58.920
Actually something I'm gonna
need you to take a look at.

12:03.000 --> 12:04.460
What are you doing?

12:04.460 --> 12:05.790
We're not finished.

12:05.790 --> 12:07.250
We finished.

12:07.250 --> 12:09.080
Well,
let's finish again.

12:09.080 --> 12:11.210
Did you not hear me say
I have work for you?

12:13.500 --> 12:14.750
Yes, ma'am.

12:17.540 --> 12:19.420
[ Sighs ]

12:19.420 --> 12:22.250
Okay.
Get back in here.

12:22.250 --> 12:23.790
[ Grunts ]

12:23.790 --> 12:25.330
Work can wait
till morning.

12:25.330 --> 12:27.580
I'm sorry.

12:27.580 --> 12:29.380
I am.

12:29.380 --> 12:30.830
[ Scoffs ]

12:33.460 --> 12:35.830
I thought we were clear
about what this was.

12:35.830 --> 12:37.960
I think "convenient"
was the word.

12:37.960 --> 12:42.120
Along with "safe."
And "secure."

12:42.120 --> 12:43.290
"Easy."

12:43.290 --> 12:44.790
So, why are you
making it difficult?

12:47.290 --> 12:48.750
[ Sighs ]

12:50.210 --> 12:52.420
Let's finish.

12:52.420 --> 13:00.830
♪♪

13:00.830 --> 13:09.210
♪♪

13:09.210 --> 13:17.790
♪♪

13:17.790 --> 13:20.620
[ Breathes heavily ]

13:20.620 --> 13:22.670
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

13:22.670 --> 13:24.290
Reporter:
As the deadline draws near,

13:24.290 --> 13:26.710
President Grant's ambitious
backing of the Vargas bill

13:26.710 --> 13:29.670
seems as though it may remain
only that -- ambitious.

13:29.670 --> 13:32.960
The former President Grant is
keeping his opinion to himself.

13:32.960 --> 13:35.380
When reached for comment
at his residence in Vermont,

13:35.380 --> 13:37.540
the two-term president
declined to answer,

13:37.540 --> 13:40.960
saying "There can only be
one President at a time,

13:40.960 --> 13:42.960
and right now?
That's Mellie Grant."
[ Knock on door ]

13:42.960 --> 13:44.960
[ Door opens ]
Sources close to the President

13:44.960 --> 13:46.620
say the final vote
is far from settled,

13:46.620 --> 13:48.170
and caution against --

13:48.170 --> 13:50.080
So, I looked up
Quinn's professor.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.580
-And?
-He's definitely CIA.

13:51.580 --> 13:53.120
So, Quinn was right.

13:53.120 --> 13:54.710
According to Langley,
Stewart's one of

13:54.710 --> 13:56.540
our most valuable assets
in the Middle East.

13:56.540 --> 13:58.540
He helped the CIA thwart
four credible terror attacks

13:58.540 --> 14:00.120
in the past three years.

14:00.120 --> 14:01.960
His post at the University
of Bashran is a cover,

14:01.960 --> 14:04.040
and he's currently our most
reliable trader of information

14:04.040 --> 14:05.920
amongst our assets
in Europe and Asia.

14:05.920 --> 14:07.290
The fact that he's missing
is big.

14:07.290 --> 14:08.580
The President
has a few minutes.

14:08.580 --> 14:11.170
You can brief her,
and we can --
No.

14:11.170 --> 14:13.210
We're not gonna tell
the President about any of this.

14:13.210 --> 14:15.120
Best-case scenario,
this guy's been taken

14:15.120 --> 14:16.540
by the Bashrani Armed Forces.

14:16.540 --> 14:18.420
Psychological torture
is an art form for them.

14:18.420 --> 14:19.790
He'll talk.

14:19.790 --> 14:22.250
Or he's in the hands of
a fringe terror group,

14:22.250 --> 14:24.500
and they're carving him up
to see what he knows.

14:24.500 --> 14:26.290
He'll talk.

14:26.290 --> 14:28.250
We can't let that happen,
not in Bashran,

14:28.250 --> 14:30.040
not in a country that's this
close to having its own nukes.

14:30.040 --> 14:31.250
He's an American hero.

14:31.250 --> 14:33.710
Yes, and if we want him to
stay an American hero,

14:33.710 --> 14:35.830
we need to kill him.

14:35.830 --> 14:37.830
Jake...
[ Scoffs ]

14:37.830 --> 14:41.210
If he talks,
he's a traitor and a weapon.

14:41.210 --> 14:43.580
If the Bashranis turn him,
if he gives up his sources,

14:43.580 --> 14:47.040
he threatens the safety of
every CIA asset in the region.

14:47.040 --> 14:48.710
We need to kill him.
We need to kill him,

14:48.710 --> 14:50.540
and we need to do it
without Mellie or Quinn

14:50.540 --> 14:52.380
or anyone else in this town
knowing about it.

14:52.380 --> 14:53.670
I put together a plan.

14:53.670 --> 14:56.170
We can do this off the books
using the B613 budget.

14:56.170 --> 14:57.880
No.

14:57.880 --> 14:59.880
It's all in there.
All I need is your go-ahead.

14:59.880 --> 15:01.420
We're not killing
one of our own.

15:01.420 --> 15:03.080
They have him.

15:03.080 --> 15:04.830
He's not ours anymore.

15:04.830 --> 15:06.960
Look,
this is your call to make.

15:06.960 --> 15:09.170
But I'm here to advise you --
and my best advice?

15:09.170 --> 15:12.460
We need to do this...
quickly.

15:15.460 --> 15:16.670
I need to think about it.

15:16.670 --> 15:18.210
I said
I need to think about it.

15:18.210 --> 15:25.540
♪♪

15:25.540 --> 15:29.210
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

15:29.210 --> 15:30.500
This gets easier.

15:30.500 --> 15:32.290
Killing a patriot?

15:32.290 --> 15:33.920
Being Command.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.830
Mr. Vice President,
thank you for coming out.

15:42.830 --> 15:44.170
[ Smooches ]

15:44.170 --> 15:46.000
Coffee?
-Mmm!

15:46.000 --> 15:49.170
Always a treat
to get out of the office.

15:49.170 --> 15:50.620
How's the family?

15:50.620 --> 15:53.500
How is Emily
liking Princeton?

15:53.500 --> 15:54.620
Couldn't be happier.

15:54.620 --> 15:56.830
Excellent. Excellent!

15:56.830 --> 15:59.290
Don't think I can't
see your angle.

15:59.290 --> 16:00.670
You mean
subtly pointing out that

16:00.670 --> 16:02.960
despite your folksy taste
in restaurants,

16:02.960 --> 16:06.210
you're a Democratic senator
whose granddaughter attends

16:06.210 --> 16:08.250
one of the priciest schools
in the country?

16:08.250 --> 16:10.960
You see, Diane --
it's sharper than an angle.

16:10.960 --> 16:12.710
It's actually a point.

16:12.710 --> 16:16.540
It's not that I have anything
against the Vargas bill.

16:16.540 --> 16:18.790
Then why do I hear rumors
you're planning to oppose it?

16:18.790 --> 16:21.960
Where you go, a bushel of
other Dems will follow.

16:21.960 --> 16:25.380
They will, which is why I wanted
to speak to you personally.

16:25.380 --> 16:27.290
[ Sighs ]

16:27.290 --> 16:30.000
Free college --
It was supposed to be ours --

16:30.000 --> 16:31.380
a Democratic initiative.

16:31.380 --> 16:32.710
So, you like this bill,

16:32.710 --> 16:34.580
but you're gonna tank it
out of spite?

16:34.580 --> 16:36.580
Work with us, Cyrus.

16:36.580 --> 16:38.080
If we burn this thing now,

16:38.080 --> 16:40.920
in four years it could be your
game-changing legislation.

16:43.120 --> 16:47.290
We're barely 100 days
into Mellie's term.

16:47.290 --> 16:51.670
You want me to row against her
so that I can take my chances

16:51.670 --> 16:53.710
in a presidential election
3 1/2 years away?

16:53.710 --> 16:57.170
I want you to take
the long view.

16:57.170 --> 17:00.170
Don't hand this win
to Olivia Pope

17:00.170 --> 17:02.710
and the president she chose.

17:02.710 --> 17:04.500
You worked for a Republican,

17:04.500 --> 17:07.670
you ran as a Democratic VP
to a martyred Latino,

17:07.670 --> 17:10.710
you serve as a Republican VP
to a woman --

17:10.710 --> 17:13.210
you're gay,
you adopted a black baby,

17:13.210 --> 17:16.000
you served time for a crime
you didn't commit.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.670
You, my friend, are the liberal
dream -- every box checked.

17:21.670 --> 17:25.620
This climb doesn't end with
Vice President, Cyrus,

17:25.620 --> 17:28.210
not when you could have
the mountaintop --

17:28.210 --> 17:31.960
Not when you could be
President Beene.

17:35.250 --> 17:39.670
When you're ready to talk
about your future,

17:39.670 --> 17:42.670
give me a call.

17:45.830 --> 17:47.960
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

17:47.960 --> 17:49.330
Quinn: The White House
is on our side.

17:49.330 --> 17:51.750
Olivia Pope has promised they
will do everything they can

17:51.750 --> 17:53.170
to bring your father home,
Ms. Stewart.

17:53.170 --> 17:54.540
The second
we hear something --

17:54.540 --> 17:56.420
I am never letting him
out of my sight again.

17:56.420 --> 17:57.580
When my dad gets back,

17:57.580 --> 17:59.790
it is a university job for him,
I swear.

17:59.790 --> 18:02.880
Thank you --
thank you, all.

18:04.460 --> 18:06.670
[ Sighs ]

18:06.670 --> 18:08.040
[ Inhales sharply ]

18:08.040 --> 18:10.120
Okay, what's for lunch?
-You didn't tell her.

18:10.120 --> 18:12.000
That her father might be a spy?
Of course I didn't tell her.

18:12.000 --> 18:14.080
Ooh, let's order from
that vegan place on 18th.

18:14.080 --> 18:15.500
-Again?
-You have to tell her.

18:15.500 --> 18:17.170
That place
doesn't serve food.

18:17.170 --> 18:19.000
She didn't hire us
to play therapist, Charlie.

18:19.000 --> 18:21.080
She hired us to find her dad --
that's it.

18:21.080 --> 18:22.540
Uh, curry bowl,
save the chutney,

18:22.540 --> 18:23.880
extra yams this time.

18:23.880 --> 18:25.250
Well,
what about our kid?

18:25.250 --> 18:27.000
Are we not gonna tell our kid
who we really are,

18:27.000 --> 18:28.580
or are we gonna spend our lives
pretending?

18:28.580 --> 18:30.710
All our client wants
is to find her father.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.040
What she doesn't want,
I can assure you,

18:32.040 --> 18:33.250
is to know that
he's a spy.

18:33.250 --> 18:35.250
Have you heard back from Liv
since last night?

18:35.250 --> 18:36.710
Uh, no.

18:36.710 --> 18:38.120
She said she'd call.
Why?

18:38.120 --> 18:40.580
Just wondering.

18:40.580 --> 18:42.380
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

18:45.460 --> 18:48.120
The body
needs to come home.

18:48.120 --> 18:49.380
Huck.

18:49.380 --> 18:53.670
It won't be as easy,
bringing the body back.

18:53.670 --> 18:55.170
But his daughter
deserves a funeral.

18:58.250 --> 19:00.330
We can't be having
this conversation.

19:00.330 --> 19:02.460
Quinn doesn't know I'm here.
Nobody does.

19:02.460 --> 19:04.790
They think you're helping.

19:04.790 --> 19:07.210
Get us a body,

19:07.210 --> 19:08.790
and nobody needs to know
it was you who killed him.

19:08.790 --> 19:11.920
Why would you assume
I'd kill him?

19:11.920 --> 19:15.500
Liv, he was a spy.

19:15.500 --> 19:16.880
That's what they do
to spies who get caught.

19:16.880 --> 19:18.210
That's not
what I'm asking.

19:18.210 --> 19:21.330
I'm asking why you'd assume
I would do that?

19:21.330 --> 19:24.000
Because
you're one of them now.

19:24.000 --> 19:32.460
♪♪

19:32.460 --> 19:34.580
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

19:34.580 --> 19:36.580
[ Indistinct chatter ]

19:36.580 --> 19:39.120
♪♪

19:45.880 --> 19:47.420
You wanted to see me,
Madam President?

19:47.420 --> 19:49.500
Where are we on
Joshua Stewart?

19:49.500 --> 19:52.000
I brought the President up to
speed on our rescue plans.

19:52.000 --> 19:53.460
Our rescue plans.

19:53.460 --> 19:54.880
The President agrees that
bringing him home

19:54.880 --> 19:57.540
is the best
course of action.

19:57.540 --> 19:58.880
I need you to tell me
the point of seizing power

19:58.880 --> 20:00.210
if you can't
make the tough call.

20:00.210 --> 20:01.330
I make tough calls
all the time.

20:01.330 --> 20:03.210
Do you?

20:03.210 --> 20:04.540
You want to ask Luna Vargas
about me?

20:04.540 --> 20:06.620
Yes. You murdered Luna
in the best way possible.

20:06.620 --> 20:09.710
You made one tough, dark,
amazing call -- one.

20:09.710 --> 20:11.040
I liked it.
I respected it.

20:11.040 --> 20:13.540
But it was one call.

20:13.540 --> 20:15.290
There are gonna be 1,000 more.
Do you have another call in you?

20:15.290 --> 20:17.250
I'm making another call.
This is my call.

20:17.250 --> 20:19.620
My call is no matter what,
Professor Stewart is a patriot.

20:19.620 --> 20:21.330
My call is
we bring patriots home.

20:21.330 --> 20:23.420
My call is
hope over cynicism.

20:23.420 --> 20:25.380
My call...

20:25.380 --> 20:27.540
is murder will not be policy
in my White House.

20:27.540 --> 20:30.040
Except we're not talking about
your White House, Liv.

20:30.040 --> 20:32.580
[ Softly ] We're talking about
B613, your B613,

20:32.580 --> 20:34.790
because that's the real job --

20:34.790 --> 20:37.460
rebuilding B613,
hiring agents,

20:37.460 --> 20:40.330
creating infrastructure,
protecting the Republic.

20:40.330 --> 20:42.250
You want
a hopeful White House?

20:42.250 --> 20:43.460
That's fine for you
when you are Chief of Staff.

20:43.460 --> 20:45.210
Pick daisies and dance.

20:45.210 --> 20:46.620
But your job as Command --
-Careful.

20:46.620 --> 20:49.420
Olivia, j--

20:49.420 --> 20:51.960
I'm trying to help.
When your father started B613 --

20:51.960 --> 20:53.710
This isn't
my father's B613.

20:53.710 --> 20:56.210
It's mine.
I run this show. I decide.

20:56.210 --> 20:58.210
You? Do what I say.

20:58.210 --> 21:01.040
Bring my guy home alive,
Admiral Ballard -- now.

21:03.120 --> 21:04.790
[ Normal voice ]
Whatever you say.

21:14.580 --> 21:16.460
[ Door opens ]

21:16.460 --> 21:17.920
You needed me?

21:17.920 --> 21:19.620
Where are we
with Greenwald?

21:19.620 --> 21:21.380
She's having a little trouble
remembering whether

21:21.380 --> 21:23.120
it's "party before country"
or the other way 'round,

21:23.120 --> 21:24.420
but I think I can
set her straight.

21:24.420 --> 21:25.460
You'll have to.

21:25.460 --> 21:27.250
Without her vote,
there's no bill.

21:34.460 --> 21:36.000
Was that it?

21:36.000 --> 21:39.000
No. The Rangerette
Future Leaders program

21:39.000 --> 21:41.080
is arriving
in an hour and a half.

21:41.080 --> 21:42.710
I need you to stop by,
say a few words.

21:42.710 --> 21:44.540
-The Rangerettes?
-Mellie was planning to do it,

21:44.540 --> 21:45.710
but she got pulled
into a meeting

21:45.710 --> 21:47.500
with
the Bashrani Ambassador.

21:47.500 --> 21:49.000
You're serious?

21:49.000 --> 21:51.170
You want me to meet with
the Rangerettes?

21:51.170 --> 21:52.420
Is that
going to be a problem?

21:52.420 --> 21:54.120
[ Huffs ]

21:55.620 --> 21:56.750
Liv --

21:56.750 --> 21:58.500
Because the last I checked,

21:58.500 --> 22:01.290
you're second-in-command to the
nation's first female president,

22:01.290 --> 22:03.170
and the Rangerette organization
is dedicated to

22:03.170 --> 22:05.540
the education and empowerment
of young women.

22:05.540 --> 22:08.290
But I'm inferring, based on
your barely hidden contempt,

22:08.290 --> 22:11.080
that meeting these young
future leaders of this country

22:11.080 --> 22:13.000
doesn't sound important
enough to you.

22:13.000 --> 22:14.080
Is that right?

22:16.620 --> 22:18.000
Of course it's important.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.420
I'm happy to go.

22:20.420 --> 22:22.540
Clear my afternoon for
this Rangerettes business.

22:22.540 --> 22:24.210
See if Jenkins can meet
Thursday instead.

22:24.210 --> 22:27.460
And...call Senator Greenwald
for me.

22:27.460 --> 22:29.380
Tell her I'm ready
to have that drink.

22:33.620 --> 22:35.040
Remarkable.

22:35.040 --> 22:36.920
I'm so glad you think so,
Ambassador.

22:36.920 --> 22:39.830
I've been told that
Bashrani tea is legendary.

22:39.830 --> 22:41.380
I was worried
we'd disappoint.

22:41.380 --> 22:43.460
Well, I've had nothing but
Starbucks for weeks,

22:43.460 --> 22:44.790
so I'm an easy mark.

22:44.790 --> 22:47.920
[ Chuckles ]
But this is
particularly delicious.

22:47.920 --> 22:50.170
So, Ambassador Marashi,

22:50.170 --> 22:51.960
we have ourselves in
a bit of a situation here,

22:51.960 --> 22:53.960
wouldn't you say?
-A situation?

22:53.960 --> 22:56.250
Relations between our countries
have never been better,

22:56.250 --> 22:59.040
and, big picture, we share a
common goal of a nuclear treaty.

22:59.040 --> 23:01.790
So if we can find a resolution
to this problem

23:01.790 --> 23:03.830
that makes everyone happy --

23:03.830 --> 23:05.830
Madam President,
I don't mean to interrupt,

23:05.830 --> 23:09.420
but I'm honestly not sure what
problem you're referring to.

23:09.420 --> 23:11.380
Ambassador,

23:11.380 --> 23:14.330
if American assets are being
held prisoner in Bashran,

23:14.330 --> 23:16.460
that is a problem,
a big problem.

23:16.460 --> 23:18.460
In the past,
a problem that big

23:18.460 --> 23:20.710
would most likely be solved with
costly sanctions,

23:20.710 --> 23:23.040
termination of
diplomatic relationships,

23:23.040 --> 23:25.170
and, potentially,
the full weight, might,

23:25.170 --> 23:27.540
and vengeance of
the United States Armed Forces.

23:27.540 --> 23:31.380
But, like I said,

23:31.380 --> 23:33.420
no one's looking to
stir the pot.

23:33.420 --> 23:35.830
Ah, now I understand.

23:35.830 --> 23:37.750
Good.

23:37.750 --> 23:39.210
I understand that
it must be difficult,

23:39.210 --> 23:40.830
being in a position
like yours --

23:40.830 --> 23:42.620
for such a short
amount of time.

23:42.620 --> 23:46.080
You must be being presented with
a massive amount of information

23:46.080 --> 23:47.460
and intelligence
on a daily basis,

23:47.460 --> 23:50.120
and it must be difficult
to try to figure out

23:50.120 --> 23:53.460
whether this information
and intelligence is good or bad.

23:53.460 --> 23:56.120
Don't worry -- I know
you're just doing your job.

23:56.120 --> 23:57.500
I don't take offense.

23:57.500 --> 24:00.420
But I will take another
cup of this wonderful tea.

24:04.420 --> 24:05.750
Thanks.

24:05.750 --> 24:07.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

24:07.460 --> 24:11.080
[ Conversing in
foreign language ]

24:11.080 --> 24:13.250
Has the Ambassador
brought up our asset yet?

24:13.250 --> 24:15.000
Hold on.

24:15.000 --> 24:16.710
Apparently his son,
little Farid,

24:16.710 --> 24:18.080
is getting bullied
at school.

24:18.080 --> 24:20.000
[ Clicks lips ]
Totalitarian regimes --

24:20.000 --> 24:22.580
They're just like us.

24:22.580 --> 24:25.080
This isn't working.

24:25.080 --> 24:27.420
I know you think I'm wasting
my time, but I'm not.

24:27.420 --> 24:29.250
I'm looking for
a better way.

24:29.250 --> 24:31.040
How long has
Stewart been missing?

24:31.040 --> 24:32.790
About 72 hours. Why?

24:32.790 --> 24:35.120
The first 24
are relatively easy.

24:35.120 --> 24:36.790
I got through the waterboarding
by pretending

24:36.790 --> 24:38.670
I was 6 years old again learning
to swim in the public pool.

24:38.670 --> 24:40.710
The German Chair?

24:40.710 --> 24:42.290
It's just a really intense
yoga session.

24:42.290 --> 24:45.380
The dogs, though --
You can negotiate with a human,

24:45.380 --> 24:48.420
but a hungry dog snapping at
your face, your genitals...

24:48.420 --> 24:50.880
I lasted 81 hours.

24:50.880 --> 24:54.330
Now, I was in my 20s, an officer
in the Navy in tip-top shape.

24:54.330 --> 24:56.790
This Stewart guy's
a 100-pound bookworm

24:56.790 --> 24:58.330
on the wrong side of 60.

24:58.330 --> 25:00.460
How much longer
do you think he's got?

25:00.460 --> 25:03.500
But it's not
about him anymore.

25:03.500 --> 25:05.750
This is about
the engineer in Natanz

25:05.750 --> 25:07.290
who puts them
behind schedule

25:07.290 --> 25:09.080
every time they get close
to a working nuke,

25:09.080 --> 25:10.880
the archaeologist
at Tepe Sialk

25:10.880 --> 25:13.710
who reports on troop movements
from the Isfahan Province,

25:13.710 --> 25:15.750
the palace guard
who keeps us informed

25:15.750 --> 25:16.620
on their president's
location.

25:16.620 --> 25:18.380
If they're taken,

25:18.380 --> 25:20.000
you won't have to worry about
100 Bashranis anymore,

25:20.000 --> 25:21.420
because you'll be too busy
worrying about

25:21.420 --> 25:23.710
the lives of
400 million Americans.

25:23.710 --> 25:26.380
You're not wasting time,
Liv.

25:26.380 --> 25:27.880
You're out of time,
and so are they.

25:27.880 --> 25:29.000
We need to shut this down.

25:29.000 --> 25:30.580
-No.
-Send somebody in there.

25:30.580 --> 25:31.750
We keep listening.

25:31.750 --> 25:33.830
-Liv.
-Keep listening.

25:33.830 --> 25:42.040
♪♪

25:42.040 --> 25:44.620
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

25:44.620 --> 25:49.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:49.830 --> 25:51.420
"Guess what, girls?
Here's another old, white guy."

25:51.420 --> 25:52.830
I brought hand sanitizer.

25:52.830 --> 25:56.210
Bless your pink little
valedictorian heart.

25:56.210 --> 25:58.670
10 minutes, and then you
interrupt me with a phone call.

25:58.670 --> 26:00.080
Mellie: Cyrus.

26:00.080 --> 26:01.250
Madam President.

26:01.250 --> 26:03.120
Olivia said you couldn't
field this one?

26:03.120 --> 26:04.750
Oh, I thought I was gonna be
tied up all afternoon,

26:04.750 --> 26:06.420
but change of plans,
so...

26:06.420 --> 26:09.580
Actually,
I'm glad I caught you.

26:09.580 --> 26:12.460
Mm-hmm.
I wanted to thank you for all
your help on the Vargas bill.

26:12.460 --> 26:14.330
That's quite unnecessary,
Madam President.

26:14.330 --> 26:16.290
We are gonna get this thing
passed, you and I.

26:16.290 --> 26:18.670
We are gonna honor
Frankie's legacy.

26:18.670 --> 26:21.670
Anyway, I know meeting with
everyone can be a grind.

26:21.670 --> 26:23.580
It can be --
but also the job.

26:23.580 --> 26:25.750
Just...thank you.

26:25.750 --> 26:28.080
They told me Luna Vargas
had that heart attack,

26:28.080 --> 26:31.120
and you have been at my side
ever since.

26:31.120 --> 26:32.080
And I just wanted you
to know that...

26:32.080 --> 26:34.040
[ Sighs ]

26:34.040 --> 26:35.880
I appreciate it,
is all, Cyrus.

26:35.880 --> 26:39.040
Of course,
Madam President.

26:39.040 --> 26:42.000
Look at us --
working together.

26:42.000 --> 26:43.460
-Hmm.
-[ Giggles ]

26:43.460 --> 26:45.620
It's a wonder why
we spent so many years

26:45.620 --> 26:46.920
trying to destroy each other,

26:46.920 --> 26:49.830
when all this time
we could've been friends.

26:49.830 --> 26:55.120
♪♪

26:55.120 --> 26:56.620
Okay!

26:56.620 --> 26:58.670
So, which one of you
is planning on

26:58.670 --> 27:00.540
running for president
one day?

27:00.540 --> 27:02.330
[ Girls chattering ]
-I like to see those hands.

27:02.330 --> 27:03.830
[ Mellie claps ]
That makes me very happy.

27:13.710 --> 27:15.540
This is where
I was told to stand.

27:17.670 --> 27:19.330
Your assistant wouldn't let me
wait inside your office, so --

27:19.330 --> 27:20.620
I've been trying
to call you.

27:20.620 --> 27:21.790
You shouldn't have made
Mr. Pryce wait outside.

27:21.790 --> 27:23.290
Nice of you to say.
She should've told you
to go home.

27:23.290 --> 27:25.120
But then we would've
missed out on

27:25.120 --> 27:27.420
this incredibly public
and awkward exchange.

27:27.420 --> 27:28.830
What are you doing here?

27:28.830 --> 27:30.290
Okay.
Now that you ask, uh,

27:30.290 --> 27:32.830
I came to see if you still
wanted your 30 seconds.

27:35.540 --> 27:40.000
Dinner --
you and me, tonight.

27:40.000 --> 27:41.420
You came here
to ask me out.

27:41.420 --> 27:43.500
Uh, no, I came here
for a media summit

27:43.500 --> 27:45.330
with
the Communications Office.

27:45.330 --> 27:46.620
But since I was in
the neighborhood, I figured...

27:46.620 --> 27:48.250
[ Inhales sharply ]

27:48.250 --> 27:49.290
Yes.

27:49.290 --> 27:51.170
Yes,
I came here to ask you out.

27:51.170 --> 27:52.790
You realize it's the middle
of the day?

27:52.790 --> 27:54.210
Well, I wasn't talking about
right now...

27:54.210 --> 27:55.710
[ Cellphone rings ]
...but if you insist
on being taken out

27:55.710 --> 27:58.330
for the best meal of your entire
life right this moment,

27:58.330 --> 28:00.210
I suppose I can
clear my afternoon.

28:00.210 --> 28:02.580
See?
There. You're smiling.

28:02.580 --> 28:04.120
I am, but it's nothing
to do with you.

28:04.120 --> 28:05.540
[ Scoffs ]

28:05.540 --> 28:06.710
I don't buy that
for a second.

28:09.620 --> 28:11.080
I think she was
telling the truth.

28:17.290 --> 28:18.830
Madam President,
good news.

28:18.830 --> 28:20.000
We got Blackburn.

28:20.000 --> 28:21.330
He's voting yes,
which means

28:21.330 --> 28:23.290
as soon as Cyrus
flips Greenwald, we'll be --

28:24.830 --> 28:26.420
Olivia:
Jake, what are you --

28:26.420 --> 28:28.750
You're not the only one
with good news.

28:28.750 --> 28:30.500
We've located
our missing spy.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.540
We have?

28:32.540 --> 28:34.620
We have.

28:34.620 --> 28:37.250
Admiral Ballard's team has been
able to pinpoint his location.

28:37.250 --> 28:39.080
He's being held in a compound
near the Turkish border.

28:39.080 --> 28:40.830
That is very good news.

28:40.830 --> 28:43.420
There's a SEAL Team aboard the
USS Alston in the Persian Gulf.

28:43.420 --> 28:45.120
If they start prepping now,
we can stage a rescue, and --

28:45.120 --> 28:46.170
The plan has changed.

28:46.170 --> 28:49.170
Since when?

28:49.170 --> 28:51.120
Rescue takes time.
Time means dead Americans.

28:51.120 --> 28:53.290
But Jake has taken me through
all the possible scenarios --

28:53.290 --> 28:54.750
I'm sure
he was very thorough.

28:54.750 --> 28:55.960
[ Scoffs ]

28:59.880 --> 29:01.920
So you're killing him?

29:04.580 --> 29:06.380
A surgical strike
is the best option.

29:06.380 --> 29:08.250
The only option.
If I could just
have a moment --

29:08.250 --> 29:09.880
You can't, Liv.

29:09.880 --> 29:11.330
You've made your case.
Now Jake's made his.

29:11.330 --> 29:15.580
It will be quick, quiet,
under the radar --

29:15.580 --> 29:18.000
You're killing a man who has
spent his life protecting --

29:19.880 --> 29:21.540
It's what we're doing,
Olivia.

29:23.420 --> 29:25.750
Jake, talk to me
about strike logistics.

29:25.750 --> 29:27.290
I want to know exactly how
we're gonna get this done.

29:27.290 --> 29:30.710
[ Sighs ]

29:30.710 --> 29:32.330
Here's some aerial photographs
of the compound.

29:32.330 --> 29:33.580
Mm-hmm.

29:33.580 --> 29:36.040
You'll notice
how isolated it is.

29:36.040 --> 29:37.620
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

29:37.620 --> 29:39.960
Hey.

29:39.960 --> 29:41.620
I need you to do me a favor.

29:43.670 --> 29:45.620
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

29:45.620 --> 29:47.330
We have helo touchdown.

29:47.330 --> 29:49.540
Jake: No chatter on coms.

29:49.540 --> 29:50.670
Madam President,
the coast is clear.

29:52.460 --> 29:55.040
[ Exhales sharply ]

29:55.040 --> 29:56.290
Take him out.

29:56.290 --> 29:58.290
We're a go.
Good luck, gentlemen.

29:58.290 --> 30:02.120
Ms. Pope, I hope you're here
with a case

30:02.120 --> 30:04.960
of that delicious tea your boss
served me yesterday morning.

30:04.960 --> 30:08.120
Otherwise,
I have nothing more to say.

30:08.120 --> 30:10.790
And what is this?

30:10.790 --> 30:13.250
I've always been impressed

30:13.250 --> 30:16.120
by the importance of family
in your culture.

30:16.120 --> 30:18.120
Children, parents,
it's the deepest of bonds.

30:18.120 --> 30:21.250
Their success,
your children's health,

30:21.250 --> 30:24.380
it's everything to you.

30:24.380 --> 30:28.670
Joshua Stewart --
I want him back.

30:28.670 --> 30:30.170
I told you.
We don't have him.

30:30.170 --> 30:33.920
That is live feed taken from the
scope of an M96 sniper rifle.

30:33.920 --> 30:35.710
You can stick by your lie,

30:35.710 --> 30:37.960
but you should know
the consequences.

30:37.960 --> 30:40.000
SEAL: Got movement.
Guard.

30:40.000 --> 30:41.920
-Go, go, go.
[ Gunfire ]

30:41.920 --> 30:43.920
SEAL #2: Guard down. On me.
All right.
Checking. Coming up.

30:43.920 --> 30:46.540
Woman: The target's holding cell
is down that hall.

30:46.540 --> 30:48.040
This is my son!

30:48.040 --> 30:50.460
Yes. And that hostage
is someone's father.

30:50.460 --> 30:52.620
We value family, too.

30:52.620 --> 30:58.790
♪♪

30:58.790 --> 31:00.580
Do you have a clean shot?

31:00.580 --> 31:02.620
Yeah.

31:02.620 --> 31:05.710
But we are bluffing,
right, Liv?

31:05.710 --> 31:07.170
We are bluffing?

31:11.540 --> 31:14.170
Liv? Answer me.

31:16.380 --> 31:18.460
Take the shot

31:18.460 --> 31:21.330
in five...

31:21.330 --> 31:25.380
four...

31:25.380 --> 31:27.460
three...

31:27.460 --> 31:30.330
tw--
-No!

31:30.330 --> 31:33.000
Please.
I'll make the call.

31:33.000 --> 31:34.960
Please don't do this.

31:34.960 --> 31:36.380
Please don't hurt my son.

31:36.380 --> 31:37.670
Please.

31:41.540 --> 31:42.960
[ SEAL speaks indistinctly ]

31:42.960 --> 31:44.790
Is that his cell?

31:44.790 --> 31:45.790
SEAL: All set?

31:45.790 --> 31:46.880
[ Explosion ]

31:46.880 --> 31:48.710
Go, go, go.

31:50.120 --> 31:52.670
-All clear.
-Clear.

31:52.670 --> 31:54.290
The target is not here.

31:54.290 --> 31:56.250
I repeat -- We do not have eyes
on the target.

31:56.250 --> 31:58.120
Where is he?

31:58.120 --> 31:59.790
Jake:
He must've been moved.

31:59.790 --> 32:01.540
Moved? Where?
[ Door closes ]

32:01.540 --> 32:03.460
Deeper in the compound, maybe --
I see a couple possibilities.

32:03.460 --> 32:04.670
Mellie:
Where have you been?

32:04.670 --> 32:06.380
I'm sorry to interrupt,
Madam President,

32:06.380 --> 32:08.290
but you need to take this.
-Olivia, if you can't tell,

32:08.290 --> 32:09.960
I'm a little busy at the moment.
Take a message.

32:09.960 --> 32:11.920
It's Ambassador Marashi,
Ma'am.

32:11.920 --> 32:17.460
♪♪

32:17.460 --> 32:20.120
Mr. Ambassador.

32:20.120 --> 32:29.920
♪♪

32:29.920 --> 32:32.500
Thank you,
Mr. Ambassador.

32:32.500 --> 32:39.080
♪♪

32:39.080 --> 32:40.290
Professor Stewart
has just been delivered

32:40.290 --> 32:43.790
to the United States embassy,
unharmed.

32:43.790 --> 32:45.460
Woman: Abort mission.

32:45.460 --> 32:46.960
Repeat -- abort mission.

32:53.080 --> 32:55.790
I've thought about your offer.
It makes a lot of sense.

32:55.790 --> 32:57.710
I thought
you'd see that.

32:57.710 --> 33:01.120
Unfortunately, your plan
has one significant flaw.

33:01.120 --> 33:02.380
It's wrong.

33:02.380 --> 33:03.420
Come again?

33:03.420 --> 33:05.380
Ask yourself

33:05.380 --> 33:09.000
why was free college part of
the Democrats' platform?

33:09.000 --> 33:12.540
The answer is because it's
what's good for this country.

33:12.540 --> 33:14.750
[ Taps desk ]
Diane, America needs this.

33:14.750 --> 33:17.210
And America will get it.

33:17.210 --> 33:20.500
But from the party that
promised it to her all along.

33:20.500 --> 33:24.710
This win
[Scoffs] can be ours.

33:24.710 --> 33:26.790
Come on, Cy.

33:26.790 --> 33:27.880
What's four years?

33:27.880 --> 33:31.170
It's four years too long
is what.

33:31.170 --> 33:32.960
It's four years during which

33:32.960 --> 33:34.880
every high-school freshman
in this country

33:34.880 --> 33:36.500
won't work as hard
as they might

33:36.500 --> 33:38.250
if they believed
their government

33:38.250 --> 33:39.750
gave a damn about 'em.

33:39.750 --> 33:41.540
Four years of
high-school graduates

33:41.540 --> 33:42.960
moving into low-skilled jobs

33:42.960 --> 33:45.380
because they can't afford to
take on student loans.

33:45.380 --> 33:48.120
And, yes, it's four years during
which your granddaughter,

33:48.120 --> 33:51.790
Emily, will finish
her career at Princeton

33:51.790 --> 33:53.460
without worrying for a second

33:53.460 --> 33:55.250
if her family can afford
to keep her there,

33:55.250 --> 33:59.080
after which she'll have
access to opportunities

33:59.080 --> 34:01.710
beyond what any mere
high-school graduate

34:01.710 --> 34:03.750
would even be
able to dream of.

34:03.750 --> 34:06.290
The ability to pay for college,
Diane,

34:06.290 --> 34:09.000
it's one of the many things

34:09.000 --> 34:12.080
that keeps the rich rich
and everyone else screwed.

34:12.080 --> 34:17.420
But now, right now, we have
the opportunity to fix that.

34:17.420 --> 34:21.170
We have a willing President,
an enthusiastic House,

34:21.170 --> 34:24.380
and enough Senate votes --
with your say-so --

34:24.380 --> 34:26.330
to turn this into law.

34:26.330 --> 34:28.580
So like I said,
your offer makes sense,

34:28.580 --> 34:30.040
but it's morally bankrupt.

34:30.040 --> 34:33.040
And if you
and your little cadre of cynics

34:33.040 --> 34:36.290
show up tomorrow
and vote against this bill,

34:36.290 --> 34:40.000
I promise both the President
and your constituents

34:40.000 --> 34:43.210
will hear about how
another fat-cat politician

34:43.210 --> 34:46.000
would rather
hand the other side a loss

34:46.000 --> 34:48.170
than give regular Americans
a win.

34:51.880 --> 34:53.170
[ Door opens ]

34:53.170 --> 34:59.380
So...how's that for
"taking the long view?"

35:02.330 --> 35:04.080
[ Door closes ]

35:06.880 --> 35:09.000
[ Sighs ]
I love a happy ending.

35:09.000 --> 35:11.460
I love a big,
fat paycheck.

35:11.460 --> 35:14.000
Usually the Pryce is right,

35:14.000 --> 35:17.460
but, yes, occasionally
the Pryce is wrong.

35:17.460 --> 35:19.670
and tonight I'm taking the L --
I said it couldn't be done,

35:19.670 --> 35:22.000
but I've just got word
that President Grant has

35:22.000 --> 35:24.380
all the votes she needs
in both Houses of Congress.

35:24.380 --> 35:26.750
Every American will have
the chance to go to college.

35:26.750 --> 35:28.420
I got to hand it to her --

35:28.420 --> 35:29.960
That unity ticket
she keeps talking about...

35:29.960 --> 35:31.290
[ Knock on door ]
...might be more than just ta--

35:36.210 --> 35:39.420
Hey.

35:39.420 --> 35:41.290
May I come in?

35:41.290 --> 35:42.460
No.

35:42.460 --> 35:46.170
Liv, I'm sorry.
I di-- [ Sighs ]

35:46.170 --> 35:49.830
It was wrong of me to go
to Mellie behind your back.

35:54.170 --> 35:55.750
There's no need
for you to apologize.

35:55.750 --> 35:57.750
This was my fault.

35:57.750 --> 36:00.080
That is very clear now.

36:00.080 --> 36:04.120
No. No, you were right about
the Professor, and I was wrong.

36:04.120 --> 36:06.210
Obviously I was right about
Stewart -- of course.

36:06.210 --> 36:08.210
But that's not what I'm --
[ Inhales sharply ]

36:08.210 --> 36:09.580
You overstepped.

36:09.580 --> 36:11.380
You went around me
to Mellie.

36:11.380 --> 36:12.960
That's not
about being wrong.

36:12.960 --> 36:14.580
That's about being
too comfortable.
Wait. I don't know --

36:14.580 --> 36:17.580
I made a mistake with you.

36:17.580 --> 36:22.290
We are very,
very good together.

36:22.290 --> 36:24.000
We have a skill.

36:24.000 --> 36:28.210
And...I was weak.

36:28.210 --> 36:30.420
But no matter what,

36:30.420 --> 36:34.330
I never should've let you
back in my bed.

36:34.330 --> 36:36.460
You're sleeping
with the boss.

36:36.460 --> 36:38.290
You got comfortable.

36:38.290 --> 36:39.750
You got familiar.

36:39.750 --> 36:42.000
You forgot who I am.

36:42.000 --> 36:45.120
You forgot to be afraid,
and you overstepped.

36:45.120 --> 36:47.420
Wait. Are y--

36:47.420 --> 36:49.580
You're not serious.

36:49.580 --> 36:51.460
Don't worry --
It won't happen ever again.

36:51.460 --> 36:52.920
This is over.

36:55.120 --> 36:58.080
Liv, come on.

36:58.080 --> 37:00.830
Go home to your wife,
Admiral Ballard.

37:11.540 --> 37:14.670
[ Door opens, closes ]

37:14.670 --> 37:15.790
[ Exhales sharply ]

37:15.790 --> 37:18.460
[ Cellphone ringing ]

37:24.250 --> 37:25.620
Yes?
-Olivia.

37:25.620 --> 37:27.710
Cyrus didn't take the bait.

37:27.710 --> 37:30.250
Looks like he's Team Mellie
all the way.

37:33.920 --> 37:36.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

37:43.420 --> 37:45.580
The President of Bashran
is irate

37:45.580 --> 37:48.040
and is refusing to
even discuss a nuclear treaty

37:48.040 --> 37:49.880
after our military incursion
into his country.

37:49.880 --> 37:51.670
So I've scheduled a call with
the British Prime Minister.

37:51.670 --> 37:53.170
They were at Oxford together.

37:53.170 --> 37:54.790
If anyone can help
smooth this over, it's --

37:54.790 --> 37:57.750
Why don't you call the
British Prime Minister yourself?

37:57.750 --> 37:59.420
Or would you rather
put an earpiece in my ear

37:59.420 --> 38:00.460
and feed me lines?

38:00.460 --> 38:02.620
Mellie...

38:02.620 --> 38:05.120
Here's how this works.

38:05.120 --> 38:07.250
You give me counsel,
I make decisions.

38:07.250 --> 38:09.830
You support that decision
no matter your --
No. Actually,
that's not at all --

38:09.830 --> 38:12.000
-If you ever cross me again --
-Cross you? I saved you.

38:12.000 --> 38:16.460
If I can't trust you,
then...

38:16.460 --> 38:19.120
[ Sighs ]

38:19.120 --> 38:21.120
This is my office.
-This is not your office.

38:21.120 --> 38:24.620
It belongs to the people,
to the Republic.

38:24.620 --> 38:27.120
This office is sacred.

38:27.120 --> 38:29.670
You don't own it,
you lease it --

38:29.670 --> 38:31.420
Four years with an option
for renewal.

38:31.420 --> 38:33.540
You protect it,
you serve it,

38:33.540 --> 38:35.290
and you don't decide the best
way to do that by yourself.

38:35.290 --> 38:36.920
I didn't.

38:36.920 --> 38:39.120
I listened to your advice,
and I chose a different course.

38:39.120 --> 38:40.330
And now I'm stuck
cleaning up after you,

38:40.330 --> 38:41.920
which is is why I need to
get you on the phone with

38:41.920 --> 38:43.250
the British Prime Minister.
-I don't care

38:43.250 --> 38:45.960
if this tiny dustup with Bashran
causes World War III.

38:45.960 --> 38:48.330
The only thing I care about
right now

38:48.330 --> 38:51.540
is making it crystal clear
that you follow my orders.

38:51.540 --> 38:53.290
You have my back.

38:53.290 --> 38:54.790
You don't
sneak around behind it

38:54.790 --> 38:57.210
and freelance
after I give an order.

39:01.960 --> 39:04.920
[ Scoffs ]

39:08.540 --> 39:10.170
There's three things
you need to know about me

39:10.170 --> 39:13.040
that you should already know,
but I clearly need to reiterate.

39:13.040 --> 39:18.880
One,
you do not ignore me.

39:18.880 --> 39:22.420
Because, two,
